help rand
 <strong>rand</strong> - Uniformly distributed random numbers
    This MATLAB function returns a random scalar drawn from the uniform
    distribution in the interval (0,1).

    Syntax
      X = <strong>rand</strong>
      X = <strong>rand</strong>(n)
      X = <strong>rand</strong>(sz1,...,szN)
      X = <strong>rand</strong>(sz)

      X = <strong>rand</strong>(___,typename)
      X = <strong>rand</strong>(___,"like",p)

      X = <strong>rand</strong>(s,___)

    Input Arguments
      <a href="matlab:web('C:\Program Files\MATLAB\R2024b\help/matlab/ref/rand.html#buiavoq-1-n')">n</a> - Size of square matrix
        integer value
      <a href="matlab:web('C:\Program Files\MATLAB\R2024b\help/matlab/ref/rand.html#buiavoq-1-sz1szN')">sz1,...,szN</a> - Size of each dimension (as separate arguments)
        integer values
      <a href="matlab:web('C:\Program Files\MATLAB\R2024b\help/matlab/ref/rand.html#buiavoq-1-sz')">sz</a> - Size of each dimension (as a row vector)
        integer values
      <a href="matlab:web('C:\Program Files\MATLAB\R2024b\help/matlab/ref/rand.html#buiavoq-1-typename')">typename</a> - Data type (class) to create
        "double" (default) | "single"
      <a href="matlab:web('C:\Program Files\MATLAB\R2024b\help/matlab/ref/rand.html#buiavoq-1-p')">p</a> - Prototype of array to create
        numeric array
      <a href="matlab:web('C:\Program Files\MATLAB\R2024b\help/matlab/ref/rand.html#mw_7b3a095f-0290-4394-8a40-c09de8009e3e')">s</a> - Random number stream
        RandStream object

